<p><font face="Arial">This page features up to the second weather from the 
 <A href="http://maps.google.com/?t=k&ll=<%= AppConfig.latitude %>,<%= AppConfig.longitude %>&spn=0.025701,0.036135&t=k">Beverly Cove neighborhood of
 Beverly, Mass</A> which is about 20 miles Northeast of downtown Boston.<p>
 With the exception of the radar image, all of this information comes from sensors mounted on my house.<p>
   The current conditions are updated <b>every 5 seconds</b> and the page reloads itself every 10 minutes.  The graphs are built every 15 minutes.<p>
  This website site runs on Ruby on Rails. The weather station is polled using a Java program. The database is MySQL.  Everything runs on Linux on VMware Server.<p>
